dysphoria is not about feelings in the same way that depression, bipoliar ecc... aren't about feelings. I was dignosed whith genetic depression by a professional who only needed to see me for a few sessions and get to talk/ask questions to me so that he could accurately understand what was my problem. I never got my brain scanned but there was enought proof to  diagnose me whith this mental illness, and guess what...  depression isn't about feelings, it's about my brain lacking some fondamental parts to enjoy life as you do and I need medicine to take off the edge just as people whith dysphoria need to take the necessary operations/steps to help them. Now I don't care why you transition or if you transition at all, but the statements that were made at the very start of the video, and on whitch the whole argument is based on, is very wrong. I belive that dyshoria is real, that it is problematic for the people that feel it and that it's not based on how you feel but on how you were born; personally I don't care why you transition if the end goal is to feel better whith yourself, to be able to function like a normal human beeing or ecc... unless you do it just to be quirky ( just because I think that it could be dangerous for the person involved ). I belive in nonbinary and I belive that nonbinary are trans because I have seen people colse to me and in the media struggle whith beeing assigned a specific gender when they are not but I have also seen ( i'm gonna talk about a friend of mine so this might be a specific case or not true for every one ) where they initially felt they had to be nonbinary for the way they expressed their self and didn't follow specific gender norms and even thought they felt fine as a femail they socially transition. Soon after they started to feel uneasy and revers dysphoria because they were not trans and do still now have problems whith it; they had to come back out from the closet as their assigned gender but it was very tought for them.   that said, do transition if you know that you are trans not if you feel like you are not what you are by birth. Transitioning is hard, not just phisicly but mentally as well, you woulden't want to take a medicine for an illness you don't have ( this is a metaphore btw ).
